1
00:00:00,940 --> 00:00:03,140
(Episode 53)

2
00:00:03,740 --> 00:00:05,580
- Seo Rin.
- You're wrong.

3
00:00:06,280 --> 00:00:08,850
I'm not Seo Rin. I'm Jang Mi.

4
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:10,450
Oh Jang Mi.

5
00:00:10,950 --> 00:00:13,420
The same Oh Jang Mi you've been
trying so desperately to kill.

6
00:00:14,990 --> 00:00:15,990
What did you say?

7
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:21,030
You killed my dad, didn't you?
Why did you kill him?

8
00:00:21,090 --> 00:00:24,660
- Don't do this. Let me go.
- Tell me why you killed him.

9
00:00:25,060 --> 00:00:27,300
Why did you have
my innocent father killed?

10
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:30,170
Manager Lee forced my father to drink
and then killed him.

11
00:00:30,340 --> 00:00:33,200
That was on your orders, wasn't it?

12
00:00:33,610 --> 00:00:35,140
Please, let me live.

13
00:00:35,140 --> 00:00:37,080
Let go of me and talk.

14
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:40,480
Die!

15
00:00:41,610 --> 00:00:43,650
You had my father killed,

16
00:00:43,650 --> 00:00:45,150
so you deserve to die too.

17
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:47,090
You're going to die just like he did!

18
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:49,150
Please, don't kill me.

19
00:00:49,350 --> 00:00:52,660
Is sending you to jail going
to bring my father back?

20
00:00:53,020 --> 00:00:55,630
You're going to suffer the same way.
The exact same way!

21
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:58,460
Let go of me...

22
00:00:58,460 --> 00:00:59,560
You monster!

23
00:01:00,670 --> 00:01:03,000
You tried to kill me,
but you hurt Seo Rin instead, didn't you?

24
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:05,470
You knew that we were twins.

25
00:01:05,970 --> 00:01:07,740
That's why you tried to get rid of me!

26
00:01:07,740 --> 00:01:09,570
No, I swear...

27
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:15,880
You even barred me from the hotel
so I wouldn't run into Seo Rin.

28
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:17,950
You were afraid our secret about
being twins would get out.

29
00:01:29,260 --> 00:01:31,430
You're pretty good at figuring things out,
aren't you?

30
00:01:34,030 --> 00:01:35,070
That's right.

31
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:37,640
My dad must have run into Seo Rin.

32
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:40,670
And that's how he found out
that we were twins.

33
00:01:41,540 --> 00:01:43,610
So to keep that a secret,

34
00:01:43,980 --> 00:01:46,240
you had my father killed, right?

35
00:01:46,980 --> 00:01:47,980
Bingo.

36
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:51,850
Why would you do that?

37
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:55,250
Why were you so desperate
to hide that we're twins?

38
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:56,250
Why?

39
00:01:56,820 --> 00:02:00,730
Did stealing Seo Rin away
from my mother make you happy?

40
00:02:01,130 --> 00:02:04,600
Are you having a blast
living as Grandpa's daughter-in-law now?

41
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:08,400
Is this why you stole Seo Rin from my mom
just to live like this?

42
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:10,970
Even going so far as to hurt my mother...

43
00:02:12,070 --> 00:02:13,840
You're smarter than I gave you credit for.

44
00:02:15,110 --> 00:02:18,640
Then again, if you're Seo Rin's twin,
I guess you'd be just as smart.

45
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:20,880
Seo Rin was clever too, you know.

46
00:02:20,950 --> 00:02:22,050
"Was?"

47
00:02:22,850 --> 00:02:26,620
Does that mean you know
what happened to Seo Rin?

48
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:27,750
I do.

49
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:30,420
She's fighting for her life in your place.

50
00:02:31,660 --> 00:02:33,890
You're so lucky.

51
00:02:33,890 --> 00:02:35,660
Shut up, you evil monster!

52
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:40,970
You raised her yourself for 30 years.
Seo Rin was your daughter.

53
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:43,600
And yet, she was hurt because of you.

54
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:46,200
How can you be such a monster?

55
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,510
How?

56
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:56,080
If you were in my shoes,
you'd do the same thing.

57
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:58,320
People aren't born evil.

58
00:02:58,450 --> 00:03:00,180
Their circumstances make them that way.

59
00:03:00,950 --> 00:03:02,450
You shameless monster!

60
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:04,590
You're a devil in disguise!

61
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,930
You're not blind,
so you saw what happened.

62
00:03:07,260 --> 00:03:09,390
Because you took Seo Rin away
from my mother,

63
00:03:09,390 --> 00:03:11,100
she's ended up like this!

64
00:03:11,530 --> 00:03:13,330
How could you tear a child
from her mother...

65
00:03:13,330 --> 00:03:16,170
and raise her as your own?

66
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:22,240
Why not? What was stopping me?

67
00:03:23,940 --> 00:03:25,640
Do you think I'm just going
to let you get away with this?

68
00:03:25,910 --> 00:03:28,950
For my mother's suffering
and for my father's life,

69
00:03:29,410 --> 00:03:31,820
I'll make you pay for everything!

70
00:03:31,820 --> 00:03:32,820
You just wait!

71
00:04:00,350 --> 00:04:03,510
Did Baek Ho go to see Oh Jang Mi
first thing this morning?

72
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:06,180
Just let him be. I've given up on him.

73
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:09,950
Honestly, we should give Baek Ho an award
for his unwavering devotion.

74
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:12,090
That kid, I swear.

75
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:14,890
He got that from you, you know.

76
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:18,560
You never had eyes for anyone else.

77
00:04:18,630 --> 00:04:21,670
Just loyal to one woman to a fault.

78
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:26,570
My goodness, he's your spitting image.

79
00:04:26,570 --> 00:04:28,070
He acts the exact same way.

80
00:04:50,830 --> 00:04:53,260
- Grandfather.
- Hey!

81
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,070
Come in, sweetheart.

82
00:04:57,340 --> 00:04:59,270
Is there something you need?

83
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:01,110
You can tell me anything.

84
00:05:02,170 --> 00:05:05,480
Grandfather, it's about my cell phone.

85
00:05:06,610 --> 00:05:10,920
Mom clearly told me she threw it away
because it was broken,

86
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:12,550
but when she was on the phone
with someone,

87
00:05:13,050 --> 00:05:15,420
I heard her ask when the phone was
going to be fixed.

88
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:17,620
I just thought that was a little strange.

89
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:18,890
What?

90
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:22,630
I'll have a word with your mother
about it.

91
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:27,600
It's not right for her to go through
her own kid's phone like that.

92
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:30,470
I know, right?
Grandfather, you're the best!

93
00:05:36,470 --> 00:05:38,210
Thank you, Grandfather.

94
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:44,080
What could this be about?

95
00:05:48,090 --> 00:05:49,090
Yes, Father.

96
00:05:51,790 --> 00:05:53,020
Ma'am, we have a huge problem.

97
00:05:53,790 --> 00:05:55,090
What are you talking about?

98
00:05:55,630 --> 00:05:58,030
You took Seo Rin's phone
from the repair shop?

99
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:11,110
She may be your daughter,

100
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:14,110
but it's not right to snoop
through a grown woman's phone.

101
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:17,050
Snooping? No, I was just...

102
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,580
What did the doctor say?

103
00:06:18,850 --> 00:06:20,420
He told you not to be so impatient.

104
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:23,090
Her memories will all come back
soon enough,

105
00:06:23,590 --> 00:06:25,190
so stop pressuring Seo Rin.

106
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:26,520
Yes, Father.

107
00:06:26,590 --> 00:06:28,590
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

108
00:06:28,730 --> 00:06:30,760
I was on my way out of the repair shop
with Director Ma's phone,

109
00:06:31,060 --> 00:06:33,330
but Secretary Kim was waiting for me,
so I had no choice.

110
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:36,900
You're right. Refusing to hand it over
would've looked more suspicious.

111
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:41,440
But how did Father know
I was having Seo Rin's phone repaired?

112
00:06:43,110 --> 00:06:44,710
Anyway, that sly old fox.

113
00:06:45,210 --> 00:06:47,450
I can't let my guard down for one second.

114
00:06:48,710 --> 00:06:51,180
If Director Ma really met Oh Jang Mi,

115
00:06:51,820 --> 00:06:53,580
her phone is sure
to have Oh Jang Mi's contact information.

116
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:57,290
What if she finds it on the phone
and tries to contact Oh Jang Mi?

117
00:06:57,890 --> 00:06:58,890
That's what I'm worried about.

118
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:02,830
If any of Oh Jang Mi's family
sees Seo Rin,

119
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:06,100
they'll find out
they're twins immediately.

120
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,070
That would be a disaster.

121
00:07:08,230 --> 00:07:10,740
Before that happens,
we have to get rid of Oh Jang Mi's phone.

122
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,670
- We're out of time, so let's move fast.
- Understood.

123
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:17,910
(Oh Jang Mi)

124
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,080
If Chae Hwa Young had seen this,
it would've been a huge mess.

125
00:07:20,810 --> 00:07:22,980
She almost found out that we met.

126
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:26,680
(Delete, Select Item)

127
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:29,150
(All Selected)

128
00:07:29,150 --> 00:07:30,350
(Delete all calls?)

129
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:35,590
There might still be evidence
in a voice recording or in the cloud.

130
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:04,560
Jang Mi,
who in the world were you going to meet?

131
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,560
Tae Sook, listen.

132
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:17,130
Jang Mi's phone is completely dead.
I should take it to a repair center.

133
00:08:17,370 --> 00:08:20,200
We don't even know when she'll wake up.

134
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,940
What's the point? Just leave it.

135
00:08:22,370 --> 00:08:24,640
Don't worry. I'll drop it off on my way.

136
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:27,010
I'll be back tomorrow.

137
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:32,150
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

138
00:08:34,820 --> 00:08:35,950
Oh, my.

139
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:37,260
Ma'am.

140
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:39,120
What brings you here?

141
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:41,490
Well... I heard Manager Lee...

142
00:08:41,830 --> 00:08:44,230
ran into Tae Pyung at the hospital.

143
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,000
I heard Jang Mi was seriously injured.

144
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,300
Yes.

145
00:08:49,770 --> 00:08:50,800
I'm so sorry to hear that.

146
00:08:51,070 --> 00:08:53,700
So how is she doing?

147
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:55,140
The surgery went well,

148
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:57,380
but she hasn't woken up yet.

149
00:09:01,180 --> 00:09:02,610
I'm sure she'll wake up.

150
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:04,650
Don't you worry, Tae Sook.

151
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:06,980
Thank you.

152
00:09:08,650 --> 00:09:10,350
What excuse can I use to get inside?

153
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:16,260
Oh my gosh, are you okay?

154
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:17,300
I feel dizzy.

155
00:09:17,860 --> 00:09:19,200
It must be my anemia.

156
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,770
I think I need to lie down for a minute.

157
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,800
Oh, dear, come inside.

158
00:09:24,870 --> 00:09:25,870
Right this way.

159
00:09:26,740 --> 00:09:28,140
Here, have some water.

160
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:36,910
I don't see Tae Pyung or Jang Mi's mother.

161
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:40,950
My mom wanted to see Jang Mi,
so they went to the hospital.

162
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:43,720
That's a relief.

163
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,120
I'm sorry?

164
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:49,960
I was worried that Jang Mi's mother
might have fallen ill from the shock.

165
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:51,200
I see.

166
00:09:52,430 --> 00:09:55,900
How's your dizziness?
Are you feeling any better now?

167
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:58,570
I'll just rest for a bit before I go.

168
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,510
Tae Sook, you should get back
to your store.

169
00:10:01,970 --> 00:10:04,340
I'm keeping you from your business.
This isn't right.

170
00:10:04,780 --> 00:10:06,210
No, don't worry about it.

171
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:09,680
Go. Just get out of here!

172
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:13,050
No, really. I feel bad holding you up.

173
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:16,450
How about you pack up some side dishes
for me to take home?

174
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:20,620
Then I'll pack the usual for you.

175
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:21,760
Thanks.

176
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:34,670
That was Oh Jang Mi's room, right?

177
00:10:56,260 --> 00:10:59,460
Darn it. Where is her phone?

178
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:02,330
Mom, you said you wanted to see Jang Mi,
so I brought you to see her.

179
00:11:02,670 --> 00:11:05,000
So why are you going on
about Tok Hee again?

180
00:11:11,210 --> 00:11:13,080
A burglar!

181
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,680
A burglar's here!

182
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:17,780
Wait, CEO Chae...

183
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:19,950
What are you doing here?

184
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:24,420
She's a burglar.
She's here to steal something!

185
00:11:24,490 --> 00:11:25,860
She's a very bad burglar.

186
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:27,430
Mom, stop.

187
00:11:27,690 --> 00:11:29,030
CEO Chae?

188
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:30,190
What do you mean, a burglar?

189
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:33,600
For goodness' sake.

190
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:37,100
I was just trying to call Manager Lee
to bring the car around,

191
00:11:37,270 --> 00:11:39,140
but my battery died.
I was just trying to charge it,

192
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:42,170
but I've become a thief now.

193
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:44,380
I am so sorry.

194
00:11:44,810 --> 00:11:47,180
My mother isn't well.
I apologize for her behavior.

195
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:50,580
Mom, that's enough.
Why are you treating her like this?

196
00:11:51,350 --> 00:11:53,380
She's a burglar. She's a bad thief.

197
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:54,750
She's here to steal something!

198
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:56,390
- Mom.
- Mom, stop...

199
00:12:00,690 --> 00:12:01,690
Yes, Father.

200
00:12:03,090 --> 00:12:04,100
Yes.

201
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:06,630
Right. Today's the day
Seo Rin has her appointment.

202
00:12:06,630 --> 00:12:07,900
I totally forgot.

203
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,170
I'll take her there right away.

204
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:22,580
I wish Baek Ho would move on
and meet another woman.

205
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:27,020
But the woman he loves
is lying in a hospital bed.

206
00:12:27,850 --> 00:12:29,750
Do you really think
he would even consider it?

207
00:12:29,890 --> 00:12:33,020
Remember that one lovely young woman
I keep telling you about?

208
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:37,430
The one who came by the office
the other day?

209
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,600
- Hello.
- Oh my, Hong Ju.

210
00:12:47,670 --> 00:12:49,440
Oh, dear.

211
00:12:49,770 --> 00:12:53,140
I think Baek Ho went
to the hospital to see her again.

212
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:54,610
I see.

213
00:12:55,450 --> 00:12:59,480
It seems Lawyer Kang is never here
when I come to visit.

214
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:01,890
He's either at the hospital
or at her house.

215
00:13:02,390 --> 00:13:05,560
He's such a mess.
I wonder how he gets any work done.

216
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:08,490
We've met at a meeting before, haven't we?

217
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:10,660
Yes, hello, Professor.

218
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:11,830
That's right.

219
00:13:11,930 --> 00:13:15,800
You two must have met while working
on the Dream Hotel project.

220
00:13:16,270 --> 00:13:17,270
Yes.

221
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:22,010
By any chance, do you know
which hospital Oh Jang Mi is in?

222
00:13:22,610 --> 00:13:23,940
(General Surgeon Kim Jung In)

223
00:13:24,070 --> 00:13:25,180
Good.

224
00:13:25,310 --> 00:13:26,980
Her progress is looking very good.

225
00:13:28,510 --> 00:13:29,580
Doctor, I was wondering...

226
00:13:30,050 --> 00:13:33,550
if she could come to the office
and slowly get back to work.

227
00:13:34,050 --> 00:13:38,520
I thought working with someone she likes
might help her get better.

228
00:13:39,090 --> 00:13:40,260
"Someone she likes?"

229
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:43,960
As long as she doesn't overdo it,
working a little bit should be fine.

230
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:46,530
The stimulation from daily life
could be good for her.

231
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:02,480
(Name: Oh Jang Mi)

232
00:14:03,150 --> 00:14:04,280
Oh Jang Mi.

233
00:14:06,620 --> 00:14:07,620
Welcome.

234
00:14:08,590 --> 00:14:12,820
No way.
Lawyer Kang is dating a woman like her?

235
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:20,760
Oh Jang Mi.

236
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:24,440
How can you be lying here like this?
You were so healthy.

237
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:27,570
They say,
"You never know what life has in store."

238
00:14:27,710 --> 00:14:29,110
I guess that saying is spot on.

239
00:14:29,710 --> 00:14:32,010
Well, it worked in my favor.

240
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:36,550
(Exam Room 1)

241
00:14:37,010 --> 00:14:40,050
Mom, I'm just going to run
to the restroom.

242
00:14:40,620 --> 00:14:42,620
Okay, sure. I'll wait here.

243
00:15:11,350 --> 00:15:12,350
Seo Rin.

244
00:15:13,420 --> 00:15:14,420
I'm here.

245
00:15:15,420 --> 00:15:16,420
It's me, Oh Jang Mi.

246
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:20,820
Please open your eyes, okay?

247
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:26,600
How can you just keep
lying here like this?

248
00:15:32,970 --> 00:15:34,840
Did you check Oh Jang Mi's hospital room?

249
00:15:35,710 --> 00:15:36,710
How is she?

250
00:15:36,710 --> 00:15:38,840
She is still the same,
with no signs of waking up.

251
00:15:39,710 --> 00:15:41,450
But it seems the hospital bills
were becoming a problem.

252
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:43,910
They moved her from the ICU
to a regular room.

253
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:45,320
I figured as much.

254
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:48,750
By the way,
I just saw Kang Baek Ho leaving.

255
00:15:49,150 --> 00:15:51,260
You should leave soon
so you don't run into him.

256
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:54,060
What? Kang Baek Ho was here?

257
00:15:56,830 --> 00:15:58,430
Seo Rin just went to the restroom.

258
00:15:58,630 --> 00:16:00,530
What if they run into each other?

259
00:16:01,470 --> 00:16:02,830
I'll go find her right away.

260
00:16:06,770 --> 00:16:08,540
Where did Baek Ho go?

261
00:16:09,070 --> 00:16:11,140
His mother definitely said
he went to the hospital.

262
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:21,720
There he is.

263
00:16:22,020 --> 00:16:23,990
It looks like fate wants
to bring Baek Ho and me together.

264
00:16:25,060 --> 00:16:27,320
He's so incredibly handsome.

265
00:16:31,860 --> 00:16:32,930
Oh, gosh.

266
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:34,700
Aren't you Lawyer Kang Baek Ho?

267
00:16:35,530 --> 00:16:36,570
What are you doing here?

268
00:16:36,570 --> 00:16:39,840
Fancy seeing you here.
It's a complete coincidence today.

269
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:41,610
Just a coincidence.

270
00:16:41,710 --> 00:16:43,440
Since fate seems
to keep bringing us together,

271
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:45,440
please take my business card.

272
00:16:47,410 --> 00:16:49,380
(Jin Hong Ju, Team Leader
of Food and Beverage, Dream Hotel)

273
00:16:49,580 --> 00:16:51,080
So you work at Dream Hotel.

274
00:16:52,420 --> 00:16:53,420
Yes.

275
00:16:56,950 --> 00:16:58,520
Are you here to see someone?

276
00:16:58,660 --> 00:17:01,990
I had some business here as well.
What a coincidence.

277
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:04,260
Well...

278
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:09,230
Being in a hospital really makes me
appreciate my health.

279
00:17:09,470 --> 00:17:10,500
Oh, right.

280
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:14,340
You were at our hotel's reopening party,
right?

281
00:17:14,940 --> 00:17:16,010
How did you know that?

282
00:17:16,010 --> 00:17:20,480
For the renewal,
I worked with Professor Kang Nam Bong.

283
00:17:21,510 --> 00:17:22,850
I was actually the one
who sent out the invitation.

284
00:17:23,380 --> 00:17:26,080
And it turned out you were there
as Professor Kang's son.

285
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:29,050
Yes, that's right.

286
00:17:30,390 --> 00:17:31,520
I recently heard the news...

287
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:33,990
about what happened to Professor Kang.

288
00:17:34,830 --> 00:17:36,490
He must have been going through a lot.

289
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:40,930
- Well, he has.
- How is Professor Kang doing now?

290
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:44,600
I'd like to pay him a visit
and formally offer my condolences.

291
00:17:45,470 --> 00:17:48,140
- But I'd be intruding, wouldn't I?
- That won't be necessary.

292
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:52,480
Gosh, he's completely shutting me down.

293
00:17:55,010 --> 00:17:57,480
If we ever meet next time,
buy me a coffee.

294
00:18:03,590 --> 00:18:05,190
How humiliating.

295
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,390
He doesn't give an inch, does he?

296
00:18:08,330 --> 00:18:12,400
Then again, the woman he loves
is lying there in a vegetative state,

297
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:14,330
so it's not like he's going to be looking
at other women.

298
00:18:14,930 --> 00:18:16,400
He wouldn't be charming
if he moved on that quickly.

299
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:20,640
One day, I'm going to make him mine.

300
00:18:48,730 --> 00:18:49,730
Yes, ma'am.

301
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,970
Seo Rin is not
in Oh Jang Mi's hospital room.

302
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:54,710
I don't think
she'll run into Kang Baek Ho.

303
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:56,970
Baek Ho came here?

304
00:18:58,180 --> 00:18:59,180
Don't worry about it.

305
00:18:59,840 --> 00:19:02,210
I'm sure Seo Rin
couldn't have found out about that.

306
00:19:03,950 --> 00:19:07,380
How could she know that we're the ones
who killed Oh Jang Mi's father?

307
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:11,290
Even if Seo Rin has met with Oh Jang Mi,

308
00:19:12,390 --> 00:19:14,590
there's no way she could find out
about the Oh Bok Gil case.

309
00:19:16,890 --> 00:19:20,060
Chae Hwa Young,
I'm sure you killed my father.

310
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:22,970
I swear I will tear you to shreds.

311
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:29,110
I miss Ok Hee and Tok Hee.

312
00:19:29,770 --> 00:19:31,740
Jang Mi was here too.

313
00:19:32,810 --> 00:19:35,050
Tok Hee is hurting.

314
00:19:35,650 --> 00:19:37,050
Suk Hee's daughters, Ok Hee and Tok Hee.

315
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:38,880
I met Ok Hee and Tok Hee.

316
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,350
We're together!

317
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,400
Mom.

318
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:56,170
Why are you out here again?

319
00:19:56,230 --> 00:19:58,540
If we lose you too,
we won't be able to go on.

320
00:19:58,600 --> 00:19:59,900
Tok Hee is hurting.

321
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:01,770
Suk Hee is sad.

322
00:20:02,210 --> 00:20:04,580
That's right, Mom.
Jang Mi is hurting right now.

323
00:20:04,910 --> 00:20:06,940
But she's going to wake up soon.

324
00:20:08,410 --> 00:20:10,080
Here, Mom. Have some of this.

325
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,020
With Jang Mi gone,

326
00:20:13,350 --> 00:20:14,990
it's just too much to handle, Tae Pyung.

327
00:20:15,550 --> 00:20:16,720
It's all thanks to Jang Mi...

328
00:20:17,090 --> 00:20:18,790
that we've been able
to take care of Mom and get by.

329
00:20:20,090 --> 00:20:21,290
It's okay.

330
00:20:25,830 --> 00:20:28,030
Manager Lee, you can go. I'll drive.

331
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:29,300
Seo Rin.

332
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:32,470
I just want to see
if I'm okay to drive now.

333
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:35,670
I want to be alone with Mom at the park,

334
00:20:35,670 --> 00:20:37,140
so please give us space, Manager Lee.

335
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:39,640
I'm okay.

336
00:20:39,710 --> 00:20:41,040
Are you sure?

337
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:42,510
You're really okay to drive?

338
00:20:42,710 --> 00:20:43,850
I'll take it slow.

339
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:48,090
You have a meeting at 3 p.m., ma'am.

340
00:20:48,650 --> 00:20:50,390
The Chairman and the board of directors
will be there,

341
00:20:50,390 --> 00:20:51,860
so you absolutely can't be late.

342
00:20:52,190 --> 00:20:53,290
- Okay.
- Don't worry.

343
00:20:53,290 --> 00:20:55,060
We're just going to pop over
to the place nearby.

344
00:21:17,810 --> 00:21:19,450
I can finally breathe.

345
00:21:20,020 --> 00:21:21,650
I felt so cooped up.

346
00:21:21,950 --> 00:21:24,920
After being cooped up working,
it feels great to get some fresh air.

347
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:28,760
The air is so nice here.
Let's take a walk in the park.

348
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:31,130
Sure. Let me get my purse.

349
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:34,500
What? Why are you grabbing your purse?

350
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:36,170
I thought we'd walk light.

351
00:21:36,230 --> 00:21:38,640
- My phone is in my bag.
- Come on, Mom.

352
00:21:40,370 --> 00:21:44,070
Let's take a break from the tyranny
of our phones and just relax.

353
00:21:44,140 --> 00:21:47,410
We came here to unwind.
Let's just clear our heads, okay?

354
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:49,550
I guess you're right.

355
00:21:50,010 --> 00:21:53,180
The meeting is at 3 p.m.,
so we'll be fine if we leave around 2 p.m.

356
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:57,090
Until then, let's not take any calls
and just enjoy ourselves, okay?

357
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:58,260
Okay.

358
00:22:07,730 --> 00:22:09,000
This feels good.

359
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:11,370
It's nice, isn't it?

360
00:22:16,340 --> 00:22:18,640
That's right. Enjoy it while it lasts.

361
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:21,980
I'm going to run to the restroom.
Get some rest here.

362
00:22:22,110 --> 00:22:23,210
Okay, go ahead.

363
00:22:36,730 --> 00:22:39,130
Hello, I'd like to report
an illegally parked car.

364
00:22:39,700 --> 00:22:40,830
The license plate number is...

365
00:22:48,540 --> 00:22:49,840
I wonder what time it is.

366
00:22:51,540 --> 00:22:54,410
What's taking Seo Rin so long?
She just went to the restroom.

367
00:23:13,660 --> 00:23:14,660
Seo Rin?

368
00:23:19,140 --> 00:23:20,170
Seo Rin.

369
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:21,810
Seo Rin?

370
00:23:24,540 --> 00:23:25,940
She's not here either.

371
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:28,350
Where could she have gone?

372
00:23:32,250 --> 00:23:34,280
I don't have my phone,
so I can't even call her.

373
00:23:34,750 --> 00:23:36,390
This is so frustrating.

374
00:23:37,320 --> 00:23:39,220
I have to be back at the office by 3 p.m.

375
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:42,030
Maybe she went back to the car.

376
00:23:50,670 --> 00:23:52,700
What? No way!

377
00:23:53,370 --> 00:23:55,210
Oh my gosh, what in the world is going on?

378
00:23:56,370 --> 00:23:58,040
All my stuff is in that car.

379
00:23:59,610 --> 00:24:01,380
My purse and phone...

380
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:05,620
What do I do? Hold on.

381
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,850
I need money to take a cab...

382
00:24:09,290 --> 00:24:12,120
and a phone to call someone.

383
00:24:12,890 --> 00:24:14,360
I'm losing my mind.

384
00:24:15,990 --> 00:24:17,630
And I can't be late for that meeting.

385
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,030
What do I do?

386
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:20,430
What am I going to do?

387
00:24:25,740 --> 00:24:26,940
Chae Hwa Young.

388
00:24:26,940 --> 00:24:28,240
Let's see you squirm a little.

389
00:24:31,010 --> 00:24:33,410
- Isn't Mom back yet?
- Your mom?

390
00:24:34,610 --> 00:24:35,980
She went out with you.

391
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:39,380
That's strange.
I thought she came back ahead of me.

392
00:24:45,060 --> 00:24:46,120
My legs hurt...

393
00:24:47,660 --> 00:24:49,130
I feel so dizzy.

394
00:24:49,730 --> 00:24:53,760
I can't believe Seo Rin left me.
Where did she go?

395
00:24:55,170 --> 00:24:56,200
Excuse me.

396
00:24:56,730 --> 00:24:58,470
Could I please borrow your phone?

397
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:00,200
I left mine behind.

398
00:25:00,270 --> 00:25:02,670
No, I can't lend my phone to strangers.

399
00:25:02,670 --> 00:25:04,170
I'm not looking to get scammed.

400
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,480
What? Do I look like a criminal?

401
00:25:09,550 --> 00:25:11,750
I can't believe how heartless people are.

402
00:25:15,250 --> 00:25:17,690
Excuse me, I'm not some weirdo,

403
00:25:17,950 --> 00:25:20,260
but I forgot my phone,
so could I please borrow yours?

404
00:25:25,460 --> 00:25:27,460
Where did Seo Rin go?

405
00:25:27,460 --> 00:25:28,570
Ma Seo Rin!

406
00:25:28,570 --> 00:25:30,570
Unbelievable. Gosh, my legs hurt.

407
00:25:34,910 --> 00:25:36,410
Hey, what's going on?

408
00:25:36,770 --> 00:25:39,110
You still can't get ahold of CEO Chae?

409
00:25:39,810 --> 00:25:42,210
She's keeping
the whole board of directors waiting.

410
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:45,520
- Director Ma was driving her, so...
- Why are you blaming Seo Rin?

411
00:25:45,780 --> 00:25:47,050
Is CEO Chae a child?

412
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:50,120
Can't she make it to a meeting on time
without Seo Rin?

413
00:25:50,350 --> 00:25:54,120
- I'm sorry, sir. I'll try her again.
- Forget it! Call it off.

414
00:25:54,820 --> 00:25:56,860
What's the point of having a meeting
without her?

415
00:25:58,030 --> 00:25:59,360
The nerve of her.

416
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:15,980
Seriously.

417
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:20,350
Ma Seo Rin, you were supposed
to stick with me.

418
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:38,100
My legs...

419
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:40,240
I'm freezing.

420
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:01,460
Oh my gosh!

421
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:03,560
Mom!

422
00:27:05,130 --> 00:27:07,500
What is wrong with you, Seo Rin?

423
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:10,330
Why did you put me through this?

424
00:27:11,270 --> 00:27:13,200
What happened to you? You're a mess.

425
00:27:15,070 --> 00:27:17,470
Mom, did you walk all the way here?

426
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:19,940
My legs...

427
00:27:19,940 --> 00:27:21,340
My legs are killing me.

428
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:24,350
What on earth happened?

429
00:27:25,820 --> 00:27:29,320
I went back to the bench,
and you weren't there,

430
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:32,320
so I just assumed you went to the meeting
and took a cab here.

431
00:27:32,790 --> 00:27:35,360
Our car was gone. It must've been towed
for being illegally parked.

432
00:27:35,460 --> 00:27:38,330
My phone and my purse were in that car!

433
00:27:38,330 --> 00:27:39,400
Oh my gosh.

434
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:40,530
Really?

435
00:27:41,060 --> 00:27:44,370
I just assumed you'd call Manager Lee
and handle everything.

436
00:27:44,470 --> 00:27:46,300
For someone as capable as you,
that's a piece of cake.

437
00:27:47,740 --> 00:27:49,910
You're good at everything, Mom.

438
00:28:15,930 --> 00:28:17,670
(The First Man)

439
00:28:17,730 --> 00:28:20,770
Two people with similar faces got
into a car accident at the same time?

440
00:28:21,100 --> 00:28:24,010
Ma'am, I need to talk to Director Ma
to confirm something with her.

441
00:28:24,210 --> 00:28:25,610
Could you please have her come in?

442
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:28,510
Compared to what you did
to my mom, dad, and Seo Rin,

443
00:28:28,710 --> 00:28:30,580
this pain is nothing.

444
00:28:30,580 --> 00:28:31,710
You need to suffer more.

445
00:28:32,020 --> 00:28:34,450
You tried hard to destroy the evidence,
didn't you, Chae Hwa Young?

446
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:37,550
I have to hurry and find the evidence
Seo Rin hid.

447
00:28:37,920 --> 00:28:40,120
That's the only way
I can finally take down Chae Hwa Young.

448
00:28:41,660 --> 00:28:43,660
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
